// test/Lower/m3_corpus/s08/pass.test — M5 T106 / FR-030 / SC-003.
// Auto-generated golden-diff harness paired with pass.expected.mlir.
// Asserts `nslc -emit=mlir` on the M3 Sema pass-case fixture for
// constraint s08 produces byte-identical output to the captured
// golden. Regression-guard: any visitor change that silently mutates
// lowering output for an M3 fixture flips this test red.
//
// XFAIL retired by post-merge M4 amendment #6 (2026-04-30): `nsl.seq`
// parent trait relaxed from `HasParent<"FuncOp">` to
// `ParentOneOf<["FuncOp", "ProcOp", "StateOp"]>` per S7
// (`docs/spec/nsl_lang.ebnf §8 line 850`). Seq inside proc body is
// now a verifier-clean shape; the nested `nsl.while` continues to
// satisfy its transitive-parent walk to `nsl.seq`.
//
// RUN: %nslc -emit=mlir %S/../../../sema/s08/pass.nsl > %t.actual.mlir
// RUN: diff %t.actual.mlir %S/pass.expected.mlir
